==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sederunt
<hw>Se*de"runt</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., they sat,
fr. <ets>sedere</ets> to sit.]</ety> <def>A sitting, as of a court or
other body.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>'T is pity we have not Burns's own account of that long
<qex>sederunt</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Prof. Wilson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Acts of sederunt</b></col> <fld>(Scots Law)</fld>,
<cd>ordinances of the Court of Session for the ordering of processes and
expediting of justice.</cd> <rj><au>Bell.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sedge</ent>⟦br⟧
